						               													<description>A set of expansion rules, units, and scenarios published in 1973 in the first issue of JagdPanther magazine. The expansion is currently available in PDF form as Amarillo Design Bureau has digitally rereleased all fifteen JagdPanther issues.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules revisions address the rules on fire and movement, close assault, smoke rounds, and artillery attacks (without spotters).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;New units depict forces of Finland, Belgium, Norway, Poland, Italy, France, Britain, Japan, and the United States. Additional German and Russian units are also added to the game, along with units for Korean War scenarios. The new units are supplemented by research notes and tables of organization and equipment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally, the expansion includes 35 scenarios set during World War II and the Korean War, with majority of these depicting conflicts in the European Theater. Hypothetical scenarios include a post-war conflict between Patton and Montgomery (!) and a 1955 &amp;quot;border skirmish&amp;quot; between British and Russian forces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
